This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses the scalability and elasticity of resources in a cloud computing environment. It also addresses the issue of transactional data access, which is a common concern in distributed computing. Additionally, it may belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories as it deals with the design of a data store and the challenges of managing data in a distributed environment. The Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the design choices and guarantees provided by the system. Finally, the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category may be relevant as the paper discusses the use of cloud computing for internet scale computing.
